Class IntegrityStateException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • io.dimeformat.exceptions.IntegrityStateException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class IntegrityStateException
extends java.lang.Exception
    Exception that is thrown if there is any problems with verifying the integrity of an item. Is used in those cases where it is not possible to return an instance of IntegrityState.
